    <h1>Female Endomorph Diet</h1>

    <!-- Body Description Section -->
    <h2>Body Description</h2>
    <p>Women with an endomorph body type often have a rounder, softer body with wider hips and shoulders. They tend to carry more weight in the lower body and have a higher body fat percentage, making it easier to gain weight but harder to lose it.</p>

    <!-- Food List Section -->
    <h2>Food List</h2>
    <h3>Carbohydrates</h3>
    <p>Limit to low-glycemic options like sweet potatoes, oats, and whole grains in small amounts.</p>
    <h3>Proteins</h3>
    <p>Chicken breast, fish, eggs, Greek yogurt, and legumes.</p>
    <h3>Healthy Fats</h3>
    <p>Moderate amounts of avocado, nuts, and seeds.</p>
    <h3>Fruits & Vegetables</h3>
    <p>Focus on high-fiber, low-sugar options like berries, leafy greens, and zucchini.</p>

